{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σῑτ-ίον</b>, τό, <br /> mostly in <i>plural</i> σιτία (<i>singular</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Acut.” (“Sp.”) , “de Arte” 10, “VM” 6, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 338d, “Phdr.” 241c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], and later Prose, as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Archigenes Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 8.1.15, Pythagorei cited in 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.12f, 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Abstinentia - Porphyrii Opuscula” 1.27)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; only used in Prose and Comedy: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <b>grain, corn</b>, ἤλουν ὄρθριαι τὰ σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>food made from grain, bread</b>, τούτοισι δὲ (i.e. ὀσπρίοισι) μὴ χρῆσθαι εἰ μὴ μετὰ σιτίων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Acut.” (“Sp.”) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπὸ ὀλυρέων ποιεῦνται σιτία make <b>bread</b> from spelt, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.36; σ. σφί ἐστι ἱρὰ πεσσόμενα [prev. work] 37. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> generally, <b>victuals, provisions</b> for men, opposed to χόρτος (fodder for cattle), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.94, 188, etc.\">Refs</a>]; σιτί᾽ ἡμερῶν τριῶν three days' <b>provision</b>, of soldiers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 197, “Pax” 312, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.48, 3.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. καὶ ποτά <b>food</b> and drink, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 490b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: so in <i>singular</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.10.18, etc.; ἐν τοῖς σ. τε καὶ ὄψοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 334c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ῥύφημα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης ὀξέων” 13. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> τἀν Πρυτανείῳ σ. public <b>maintenance</b> in the Prytaneum, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 709. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> rarely, <b>food</b> for dogs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 7.11. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>faces</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 355. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6079","accentedUnicode":"σιτίον","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4621","matchingForm":"σῖτος","stepTransliteration":"sitos","gloss":"grain","_zh_tw_Gloss":"麥子","_es_Gloss":"grano","_zh_Gloss":"麦子"}],"shortDef":"grain, food","mediumDef":"grain, food <br />Some manuscripts list σῖτος (G4621) in place of G6079 at <ref='Act.7.12'>Act.7.12</ref>","stepGloss":"food","stepTransliteration":"sition","count":1,"_es_Definition":"grano; pl. comida, alimento","_step_Type":"word"}]}